Ogun Police Command has mounted intense search in bushes and other places in the State for two Chinese abducted by gunmen from their farm in Oba town on Wednesday. The Chinese nationals, working with a fishery and poultry company at Oba in Obafemi Owode Local Government Area, were whisked away around noon. The Police Public Relations Officer of the Command, Abimbola Oyeyemi, told The Nation operatives are working to locate the abductees and rescue them. “We are on it, we are working to locate and rescue the victims,” he said. Abimbola, a Deputy Superintendent of Police (DSP), said the abductors accessed the farm in Oba community through Odo Ogun,(river ogun) and escaped with the captives through the same water. About a dozen of gunmen invaded the ancient Egba town of Oba-Ile around 3: 01p.m and started shooting sporadically into the air, before abducting the two Chinese nationals.